SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYSunday 13 March S10 V3 Key games in the battle against relegation from the Premier League today see Everton needing to beat Wolves while both Leeds United and Norwich City are also searching for much needed points at Elland Road. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Angers vs Stade Reims: Angers have been beaten in their last three home matches. Reims’ last away game was 2-1 win at Monaco.M2 Chelsea vs Newcastle United: Chelsea have won their last three clashes against Newcastle, two of them way from home and without conceding any goals.M3 Everton vs Wolverhampton Wanderers: Everton have won their past two home games against Wolves. Overall they have a 29-10 win count at Goodison Park against Wanderers.M4 Leeds United vs Norwich City: Leeds have 50% home success against the Canaries with 11 wins from 22 past visits. There have been seven draws and four victories at Elland Road for Norwich.M5 Southampton vs Watford: Southampton are unbeaten in their past seven clashes against the Hornets with four victories, two of them away from homeM6 West Ham United vs Aston Villa: West Ham have gone eight games without a loss against Villa, having won the past three meetings between the two claret-clad clubs.M7 Real Betis vs Athletic Bilbao: Betis’ last two home games with Bilbao were both drawn but they need a win here to keep up their hopes of playing in next season’s Champions League.M8 Orlando Pirates vs Royal Leopard: Pirates hammered the Swazi club 6-2 in their last meeting at Nelspruit and will be looking for a similarly emphatic victory at the Orlando Stadium.M9 TS Galaxy vs Baroka: Baroka beat Galaxy 1-0 in the league last weekend but now travel away for a Nedbank Cup second round tie.M10 Arsenal vs Leicester City: Arsenal’s last two home game both ended in 2-1 wins. Leicester have won their last two Premier League games but still sit in the bottom half of the log. Suggested permutation: R2.00 3 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1